WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.518 --> 00:00:02.961
<v ->David Berceli is a former monk who spent</v>

2
00:00:02.961 --> 00:00:06.065
many years of his life traveling to worn-torn nations

3
00:00:06.065 --> 00:00:08.048
to assist the people through the trauma

4
00:00:08.048 --> 00:00:10.522
and its ravaging affects on their lives.

5
00:00:10.522 --> 00:00:13.680
His work resulted in what he now calls TRE,

6
00:00:13.680 --> 00:00:17.340
or trauma release exercises, which he shares with

7
00:00:17.340 --> 00:00:20.454
veterans returning from Iraq to ordinary citizens.

8
00:00:20.454 --> 00:00:23.643
In brief, he says that the trauma is retained in our body

9
00:00:23.643 --> 00:00:26.544
long after the event, and it results in many dysfunctional

10
00:00:26.544 --> 00:00:30.053
patterns that affect our minds, bodies, and emotions.

11
00:00:30.053 --> 00:00:33.040
By releasing the body's trauma patterns, we can begin

12
00:00:33.040 --> 00:00:37.376
to heal our lives, both individually and collectively.

13
